  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and dice the<strong> brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a medium-sized pot (with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add half of the <strong>diced</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong> (save the rest for later), the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(Can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 3 min, or until the onion is softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and stir gently to coat the grains in the spices</p>\r\n<p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked &ndash; this is your <strong>spiced rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop the <strong>ginger</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly (including the stalks), reserving a few whole sprigs for garnish</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;garlic</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> to a <strong>processor</strong> with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span><strong>&nbsp;olive oil</strong>, 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span>&nbsp;of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and blitz until smooth</p>\r\n<p>Tip: alternatively use a stick blender or pestle &amp; mortar&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/424__step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
